# ============================================
# DEPLOYMENT CHECKLIST
# ============================================
# Complete these steps before going live:
#
# [ ] Database created in Hostinger
# [ ] Database credentials filled in above
# [ ] Database schema imported (complete_lms_schema.sql)
# [ ] Migration run (add_live_sessions.sql)
# [ ] Email account created and configured
# [ ] ENCRYPTION_KEY generated and filled in
# [ ] JWT_SECRET generated and filled in
# [ ] SSL certificate active (HTTPS)
# [ ] SESSION_SECURE=true (requires HTTPS)
# [ ] APP_DEBUG=false
# [ ] APP_ENV=production
# [ ] File permissions set (755 for directories)
# [ ] Web root pointing to /public/ directory
# [ ] .htaccess files in place
# [ ] Admin account created
# [ ] Test login/registration
# [ ] Test file uploads
# [ ] Test email sending
# [ ] Review error logs
# [ ] Backups configured
#
# ============================================
# QUICK SETUP GUIDE
# ============================================
#
# 1. GENERATE SECURITY KEYS (On your computer):
#    Mac/Linux:
#      openssl rand -base64 32
#      openssl rand -base64 64
#    Windows (PowerShell):
#      -join ((48..57) + (65..90) + (97..122) | Get-Random -Count 32 | ForEach-Object {[char]$_})
#
# 2. GET HOSTINGER DATABASE CREDENTIALS:
#    - Login to Hostinger
#    - Go to: Databases
#    - Create new database or use existing
#    - Note: Database name, username, password
#
# 3. SETUP EMAIL:
#    - Go to: Hostinger → Emails
#    - Create email account (e.g., noreply@yourdomain.com)
#    - Get password
#    - Fill in MAIL_* fields above
#
# 4. DEPLOY:
#    - Upload all files to Hostinger
#    - Copy this file to .env
#    - Set file permissions
#    - Import database
#    - Test!
#
